EXERCISE : Running R on AWS

1) run instance EC2  -> choose Amazon Linux AMI (provided at no additional cost)
2) choose instance type -> AMI LINUX
3) CONFIGURE INSTANCE DETAILS:
#!/bin/bash
#install R
yum install -y R
#install RStudio-Server 1.0.153
wget https://download2.rstudio.org/rstudio-server-rhel-1.1.463-x86_64.rpm
yum install -y --nogpgcheck rstudio-server-rhel-1.1.463-x86_64.rpm
rm rstudio-server-rhel-1.1.463-x86_64.rpm

#add user(s)
useradd marlena
echo marlena:proba22 | chpasswd 
